In England, in the seven days to 21 October, there were 275,621 new confirmed cases (487.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 October, there were 247,040 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 12% (28,581 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 26 October is 7,526,898 (13,310.1 cases per 100,000 population).
